{
  "stem": "14251.5",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But in German, it's Zipfel, which means corner.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So you see always the similarity?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I would guess what she was saying.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Zippella, I thought, was a boy for days on end.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And some other boy thought I was a boy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "You know, we all had the same look.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And Zippella sort of looked after me, would say, come on, come on, give me your piece of soap.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They just gave you a piece of soap when you came in here.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We didn't get baths, but we had soap.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "That would be Russian.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "You got one piece, but not the other.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "You got a car, but no tires.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And I said, I need that soap.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And she said, no, no, we have to fill the cracks, the bed bugs.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I still remember the smell of dead bed-- bed bugs.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It's a sweet, disgusting smell.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And she said, the big thing is coming.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The big day is coming.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We'll share what soap we have left.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But we must fill the cracks to keep the bed bugs out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "The minute the lights went out, the things were-- were a sea of them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "You could feel them under your feet, in your bed, everywhere.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And of course they'd bite you, as did the-- the lice and the scabies and everything else.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She said, we're going to have a ceremony soon-- it was the 1st of May, big holiday with the Russians-- and we're going to be red pioneers, you know?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "First there was the-- the Hitler Youth or the BDM, then came the Red-- Young Pioneers, Young Pioneers, and then comes the Girl Scouts and Boy Scouts.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I no longer know where I am.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we got this orange scarf.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
